- I asked you to calm down.

101
00:12:30,382 --> 00:12:31,872
Hell, no, I'm going in the club.

102
00:12:31,984 --> 00:12:34,316
Andy, step aside.
Kim, get back to the door.

103
00:12:35,087 --> 00:12:37,248
- Is there a problem?
- Damn right.

104
00:12:37,356 --> 00:12:38,880
This punk with the suntan's saying

105
00:12:38,991 --> 00:12:41,152
We can't come in the club
'cause of how we're dressed.

106
00:12:42,061 --> 00:12:43,028
Suntan.

107
00:12:44,130 --> 00:12:47,293
- And what are you guys, ballplayers?
- Yeah, semi-pro.

108
00:12:47,399 --> 00:12:49,765
- Semi-pro!
- Oh, yeah.

109
00:12:49,869 --> 00:12:50,893
Well, I'm very sorry,

110
00:12:51,003 --> 00:12:53,335
<i>but we only let professionals
in my club!</i>

111
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:55,236
Hey, ignore him! Come here!

112
00:12:55,341 --> 00:12:57,775
- You wanna come to my club?!
- Hey, get over here!

113
00:12:57,877 --> 00:13:00,471
- Calm down!
- Let me go!

114
00:13:00,579 --> 00:13:02,740
There's a van across the street.
See the van?

115
00:13:02,848 --> 00:13:05,282
It's been there since
5:30 this afternoon,

116
00:13:05,384 --> 00:13:06,817
nobody's gotten in or out of it.

117
00:13:07,987 --> 00:13:10,478
- You've been watching it since 5:30?
- Yeah. It's my job.

118
00:13:12,191 --> 00:13:13,658
- Don't look at it.
- who is this?

119
00:13:13,759 --> 00:13:16,057
<i>Could be the Enquirer,
could be the cops,</i>

120
00:13:16,162 --> 00:13:19,689
but I figured you should know
before you belted this guy in the face.

121
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:23,329
All right.

122
00:13:23,435 --> 00:13:25,096
- Handle this.
- All right.

123
00:13:29,408 --> 00:13:31,399
Let's talk for a second.
Calm down.

124
00:13:31,510 --> 00:13:34,377
Now, listen. There's a van
across the street. You see the van?

125
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:35,845
Don't look at the van.

126
00:13:35,948 --> 00:13:38,940
It's full of cops, which is why
I brought the boss back inside.

127
00:13:39,051 --> 00:13:41,246
Now, you're not getting
in this club tonight.

128
00:13:41,353 --> 00:13:44,652
<i>But... you come back here
tomorrow night dressed to impress,</i>

129
00:13:44,757 --> 00:13:47,487
I will walk you in myself,
and the club picks up the tab.

130
00:13:47,593 --> 00:13:49,925
That's the deal.
Do you want it or not?

131
00:13:50,029 --> 00:13:52,589
- VIP Room and bottle service?
- VIP Room, done.

132
00:13:53,432 --> 00:13:55,866
- All right?
- All right.

133
00:13:55,968 --> 00:13:57,492
You all right, Manny? You okay?

134
00:13:58,103 --> 00:13:59,900
Let's get this rope set back up.

135
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:01,802
- Andy.
- Yeah.

136
00:14:05,244 --> 00:14:07,838
- A blackjack? what are you gonna do?
- Let's take a walk.

137
00:14:07,947 --> 00:14:10,916
I want to see if those college boys
are the only ones who fast-talk.

138
00:14:12,251 --> 00:14:14,048
Hey, where ya goin'?!

139
00:14:20,392 --> 00:14:23,884
- what do you think?
- I think it was the cops.

140
00:14:23,996 --> 00:14:25,224
Not paparazzi?

141
00:14:25,331 --> 00:14:26,457
- Nah.
- why not?

142
00:14:26,565 --> 00:14:29,033
Paparazzi would have stayed
and took your picture.

143
00:14:29,134 --> 00:14:30,601
All right.

144
00:14:46,986 --> 00:14:48,544
Get that ready, will you?

145
00:15:11,310 --> 00:15:14,711
<i>To what do I owe the pleasure
again, Lieutenant Houlton?</i>

146
00:15:14,813 --> 00:15:18,579
I'm just feeling a little unloved because
my name wasn't on the list last night

147
00:15:18,684 --> 00:15:20,174
and I had to miss Puffy and all.

148
00:15:20,286 --> 00:15:23,084
You're looking for love?
Buy yourself a puppy dog.

149
00:15:23,188 --> 00:15:24,746
Just stop hassling my customers.

150
00:15:24,857 --> 00:15:28,520
<i>Since Liquid opened, drug arrests
on South Beach are up 20%y.</i>

151
00:15:28,627 --> 00:15:29,855
- So?
- They're club-goers.

152
00:15:29,962 --> 00:15:32,362
I don't like your people or your club
corrupting my city.

153
00:15:32,464 --> 00:15:34,796
My club is clean, and I'm clean.

154
00:15:37,136 --> 00:15:38,626
I'm gonna do you a favor.

155
00:15:38,737 --> 00:15:42,264
You wanna come in and feel the love,
I'll leave your name at the door.

156
00:15:42,374 --> 00:15:43,398
I'll take a rain check.

157
00:15:43,509 --> 00:15:46,569
But tell your buddy Madonna
and all your other fancy friends

158
00:15:46,679 --> 00:15:49,307
that I'll be there...
sooner or later.

159
00:15:49,415 --> 00:15:50,439
Okay.

160
00:15:51,684 --> 00:15:53,242
Enjoy yourself while you can.

161
00:15:53,352 --> 00:15:56,082
And I don't need my name
on your bullshit list.

162
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:17,030
Look at this. Real nice.

163
00:17:22,441 --> 00:17:24,500
- Hey, Danny.
- Yo!

164
00:17:24,610 --> 00:17:26,805
- You got a count?
- Yeah.

165
00:17:26,912 --> 00:17:30,177
About 250, minus expenses.

166
00:17:31,417 --> 00:17:34,045
Health inspectors. Code enforcement.
Sanitation boys.

167
00:17:34,153 --> 00:17:36,383
You know they jacked up
the juice again last week?

168
00:17:36,488 --> 00:17:39,423
Cost of doing business.
Don't take it personally.

169
00:17:39,525 --> 00:17:41,550
Do me a favor.
Cut me out two Gs.

170
00:17:49,334 --> 00:17:53,395
Beautiful girls, beautiful girls.
Get these two in right here.

171
00:17:57,643 --> 00:18:00,703
VIPs. I'll take care of
these two right here.

172
00:18:28,874 --> 00:18:30,603
Chris?

173
00:18:30,709 --> 00:18:32,768
Two guys are asking
to see the manager.

174
00:18:33,378 --> 00:18:34,777
All right, send 'em in.

175
00:18:44,423 --> 00:18:46,414
Are you Mr. Troiano?

176
00:18:50,195 --> 00:18:51,162
I'm Chris Troiano.

177
00:18:53,765 --> 00:18:55,960
You look just like the magazine.

178
00:18:56,068 --> 00:18:58,093
Yes, 'cause that's me.

179
00:18:58,203 --> 00:19:00,501
A friend of ours saw the picture

180
00:19:00,606 --> 00:19:03,302
and said maybe you can help us
find some people.

181
00:19:04,877 --> 00:19:07,937
- what are you guys, cops?
- Just friends.

182
00:19:08,046 --> 00:19:11,106
They are supposed to be
friends of yours.

183
00:19:11,216 --> 00:19:12,649
Do you know Mike Block?

184
00:19:14,086 --> 00:19:16,350
- Phil D'Amato?
- No.

185
00:19:16,455 --> 00:19:18,047
Davey Harris?

186
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:20,284
Tony Pizzo?

187
00:19:20,392 --> 00:19:22,622
- Eddy Boyle?
- No.

188
00:19:22,728 --> 00:19:25,424
Slava Petrov from Staten Island?

189
00:19:26,565 --> 00:19:28,533
Somebody shot his wife dead,
you know.

190
00:19:29,134 --> 00:19:30,465
Very sad.

191
00:19:32,604 --> 00:19:34,435
How about Christian wentz?

192
00:19:34,540 --> 00:19:37,941
Like you, he come from New York
to be a big shot.

193
00:19:38,043 --> 00:19:39,601
I don't know what you're talkin' about.

194
00:19:39,711 --> 00:19:43,340
The man we're looking for
takes money from Slava Petrov.

195
00:19:43,448 --> 00:19:45,609
I think the money comes to you.

196
00:19:45,717 --> 00:19:48,049
Slava Petrov's money is our money.

197
00:19:48,153 --> 00:19:50,280
Our money, our club.

198
00:19:51,323 --> 00:19:52,984
I think we partners now.

199
00:19:53,091 --> 00:19:54,422
You're talkin' bullshit.

200
00:19:56,929 --> 00:20:02,526
In the club it's okay the people
think Chris is the boss.

201
00:20:09,474 --> 00:20:11,874
But you remember...

202
00:20:11,977 --> 00:20:13,706
Who is the real boss.

203
00:20:15,180 --> 00:20:17,239
No worries, Mr. Troiano.

204
00:20:18,317 --> 00:20:20,046
I take care of this.

205
00:20:49,147 --> 00:20:50,114
Come here!

206
00:20:51,016 --> 00:20:52,278
Come here!

207
00:20:52,384 --> 00:20:53,442
Get over here!

208
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:06,798
Hold him right there!

209
00:21:08,333 --> 00:21:10,062
You piss in my club?!

210
00:21:10,168 --> 00:21:13,160
Huh?! You wanna piss in my club?!
Now I piss on you!

211
00:21:16,608 --> 00:21:18,303
Get off!

212
00:21:18,410 --> 00:21:21,573
<i>Throw 'em in the Dumpster!
I mean in the Dumpster!</i>

213
00:21:28,020 --> 00:21:31,012
You see that puddle over there?
Get all that up.

214
00:21:33,058 --> 00:21:34,025
Hey, boss.

215
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:38,186
I hope you don't mind me askin',
what was that all about?

216
00:21:38,297 --> 00:21:40,060
How do I know?
They were drunk.

217
00:21:40,165 --> 00:21:41,427
All right, they were drunk.

218
00:21:41,533 --> 00:21:44,297
Drunk or not, somebody pisses
and lights a fire in my club,

219
00:21:44,403 --> 00:21:45,700
I'd be a little bit worried.

220
00:21:45,804 --> 00:21:48,602
- Don't worry about it, all right?
- I ain't worried about it.

221
00:21:48,707 --> 00:21:51,141
- No one's burning me down.
- Good.

222
00:21:51,243 --> 00:21:53,268
I'm actually starting to like this job.

223
00:22:16,735 --> 00:22:18,168
You okay, buddy?

224
00:22:21,340 --> 00:22:22,671
How ya doin'?

225
00:22:22,774 --> 00:22:24,139
- Hey, look out!
- Hey!

226
00:22:28,413 --> 00:22:31,075
- Thank you.
- You look like you could use some help.

227
00:22:31,183 --> 00:22:32,172
I think you're right.

228
00:22:32,284 --> 00:22:35,947
Last time I was on a pair of these things,
they still called 'em skates.

229
00:22:36,054 --> 00:22:38,022
Well, the first lesson's free.

230
00:22:38,123 --> 00:22:40,455
Oh, yeah? what about after that?

231
00:22:40,559 --> 00:22:41,958
We'll negotiate.

232
00:22:42,060 --> 00:22:44,290
I can be a pretty hard negotiator.

233
00:22:44,396 --> 00:22:45,988
We'll see about that.

234
00:23:12,391 --> 00:23:15,155
Yeah. I'm only telling you
what I heard.

235
00:23:16,228 --> 00:23:17,695
- Albie.
- Yeah?

236
00:23:17,796 --> 00:23:19,354
Tell Danny and Manny
to get over here.

237
00:23:21,867 --> 00:23:24,301
- You sure about this?
- I'm tellin' you what I heard.

238
00:23:24,870 --> 00:23:25,837
All right.

239
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:31,234
Girls, would you
join me for a second?

240
00:23:31,343 --> 00:23:32,708
What's up?

241
00:23:32,811 --> 00:23:35,939
we're checkin' I.D. S tonight.
Every one of 'em.

242
00:23:36,047 --> 00:23:38,174
And I don't want to see
any candy being sold.

243
00:23:38,283 --> 00:23:39,841
Why? what's the matter?

244
00:23:39,951 --> 00:23:41,885
We're taking a raid tonight.

245
00:23:42,921 --> 00:23:45,014
- Where'd you hear that?
- Doesn't matter.

246
00:23:45,123 --> 00:23:47,455
They're gonna pretend like
they're checking I.D. S,

247
00:23:47,559 --> 00:23:49,220
but they're gonna be looking for dope.

248
00:23:49,327 --> 00:23:52,524
