00:56:43,900 --> 00:56:44,958
Hey.

742
00:56:46,836 --> 00:56:48,667
You forgot these at the club.

743
00:56:48,772 --> 00:56:51,172
You might want to be careful
next time.

744
00:57:01,885 --> 00:57:04,149
- Okay.
- Here we go. Here we go.

745
00:57:04,254 --> 00:57:05,744
Two more steps.

746
00:57:08,425 --> 00:57:10,359
One, two...

747
00:57:12,595 --> 00:57:15,223
...three.
- Surprise!

748
00:57:18,568 --> 00:57:19,933
"The bitch is back. "

749
00:57:20,970 --> 00:57:23,131
I love it. Thank you so much.

750
00:57:24,941 --> 00:57:27,569
- This is great.
- welcome back.

751
00:57:29,179 --> 00:57:31,613
It's all right. It's club soda.
Boss's orders.

752
00:57:33,183 --> 00:57:36,448
While we welcome Olivia back,
let's just take one moment,

753
00:57:36,553 --> 00:57:38,248
we gotta say good-bye to Danny,

754
00:57:38,354 --> 00:57:40,845
who's been with Liquid
from the very beginning,

755
00:57:40,957 --> 00:57:43,653
at the steering wheel,
going back home.

756
00:57:43,760 --> 00:57:46,422
We wish you nothing but luck,
my friend,

757
00:57:46,529 --> 00:57:48,292
and I don't think I'm alone
when I say:

758
00:57:48,398 --> 00:57:51,128
May all your ups and downs
be between the sheets.

759
00:57:53,470 --> 00:57:54,903
Let's have some fun, all right?

760
00:58:29,606 --> 00:58:31,471
- You guys good to go?
- Yep.

761
00:58:35,211 --> 00:58:37,975
<i>So far the police
are not telling us what led them</i>

762
00:58:38,081 --> 00:58:40,242
<i>to the black BMwluxury car</i>

763
00:58:40,350 --> 00:58:42,580
<i>at a remote park at Key Biscayne,</i>

764
00:58:42,685 --> 00:58:45,518
<i>but inside the trunk they found
the bodies of the two men</i>

765
00:58:45,622 --> 00:58:48,955
<i>identified as Alexi Papov
and Dimitri Kroutik.</i>

766
00:58:49,058 --> 00:58:51,856
<i>Police sources say
they suspect both men last night</i>

767
00:58:51,961 --> 00:58:54,122
<i>were victims of a mob-like hit,</i>

768
00:58:54,230 --> 00:58:56,630
<i>and there were bullet holes
in their car</i>

769
00:58:56,733 --> 00:58:59,998
<i>indicating there may have been
a high-speed chase</i>

770
00:59:00,103 --> 00:59:01,229
<i>before the murders.</i>

771
00:59:01,337 --> 00:59:04,170
<i>we'll be back
with more in a minute.</i>

772
00:59:07,710 --> 00:59:11,339
This wouldn't have anything to do
with our little boat trip, would it?

773
00:59:11,447 --> 00:59:13,438
How do I know?

774
00:59:13,550 --> 00:59:15,017
What do I care?

775
00:59:15,118 --> 00:59:16,608
Well, you should care.

776
00:59:16,719 --> 00:59:19,950
We could have to answer
some really important questions soon.

777
00:59:20,056 --> 00:59:21,580
What are you talking about?

778
00:59:21,691 --> 00:59:23,488
We had a brawI
with these two dead guys

779
00:59:23,593 --> 00:59:26,756
in front of a dozen witnesses,
not to mention a car chase.

780
00:59:26,863 --> 00:59:29,297
So what if the cops pull
the slugs out of that BMw

781
00:59:29,399 --> 00:59:31,560
and find they match a gun
registered to you?

782
00:59:31,668 --> 00:59:33,397
You gonna say you lost the gun?

783
00:59:33,503 --> 00:59:35,971
They're gonna say,
"why didn't you report it lost?"

784
00:59:36,072 --> 00:59:39,041
- They shot at us first.
- They're dead!

785
00:59:39,142 --> 00:59:42,441
<i>Nobody can arrest them.
They can arrest us. we're the live ones!</i>

786
00:59:43,880 --> 00:59:45,006
Think about it.

787
00:59:49,452 --> 00:59:50,783
Yeah.

788
00:59:52,755 --> 00:59:53,722
Okay.

789
00:59:54,757 --> 00:59:55,883
All right.

790
00:59:59,429 --> 01:00:01,624
I'll be right back. wait here.

791
01:00:39,702 --> 01:00:41,226
Everything all right?

792
01:00:49,879 --> 01:00:51,471
Come on, we're going for a ride.

793
01:00:52,515 --> 01:00:54,380
- Let me just grab my phone.
- No.

794
01:00:56,452 --> 01:00:57,885
You won't need it.

795
01:01:20,009 --> 01:01:21,306
Where we headin', boss?

796
01:01:47,270 --> 01:01:48,464
Get out.

797
01:02:12,295 --> 01:02:14,593
- Start walking.
- what are we doing?

798
01:02:16,999 --> 01:02:18,694
You never been to the 'glades, Andy?

799
01:02:18,801 --> 01:02:21,167
No. why would I want to?

800
01:02:23,306 --> 01:02:25,331
There's the gator.

801
01:02:25,441 --> 01:02:27,170
Maybe he smells dinner.

802
01:02:30,379 --> 01:02:31,403
Go on.

803
01:02:34,383 --> 01:02:36,544
Sometimes you gotta
feed the gators, Andy,

804
01:02:36,652 --> 01:02:39,052
<i>or they'll come out of the swamp
and eat you.</i>

805
01:02:43,593 --> 01:02:45,584
What the hell are we doing here?

806
01:02:50,600 --> 01:02:55,128
You know, back in Bath Beach,
there's two ways to stay out of trouble...

807
01:02:55,238 --> 01:02:57,468
you either pay someone off

808
01:02:57,573 --> 01:03:00,269
or make sure nothing ties you
to anything that could be trouble.

809
01:03:00,376 --> 01:03:02,742
Nothing, nobody.

810
01:03:02,845 --> 01:03:05,313
So what's that got to do with me?

811
01:03:08,351 --> 01:03:11,912
Officer Dave came by
with some disturbing news.

812
01:03:12,021 --> 01:03:13,511
Like what?

813
01:03:15,458 --> 01:03:17,016
You were right.

814
01:03:17,126 --> 01:03:19,959
They pulled some slugs out of the BMw,
just like you said.

815
01:03:20,062 --> 01:03:22,155
They're looking for a match.

816
01:03:33,342 --> 01:03:34,900
Now you're thinking.

817
01:03:36,145 --> 01:03:37,635
Look at you.

818
01:03:37,747 --> 01:03:40,272
You don't like it out here
in the boonies, do you?

819
01:03:41,117 --> 01:03:43,017
- Why would I?
- City kid.

820
01:03:43,119 --> 01:03:44,643
It's hot out here.

821
01:03:50,927 --> 01:03:51,894
Lieutenant.

822
01:03:53,362 --> 01:03:54,659
You're under the gun, Mike.

823
01:03:55,765 --> 01:03:58,598
- From you?
- Message from the chief.

824
01:03:58,701 --> 01:04:01,864
Your little pet project's
becoming a real epic saga.

825
01:04:01,971 --> 01:04:02,938
Really.

826
01:04:03,039 --> 01:04:05,269
Running up a big bill,
got nothing to show for it.

827
01:04:05,374 --> 01:04:08,810
Then we got these dead Russians,
not to mention your boy on the inside.

828
01:04:08,911 --> 01:04:10,242
what about him?

829
01:04:10,346 --> 01:04:13,338
I.A.'s been asking questions
about his conduct.

830
01:04:13,449 --> 01:04:15,644
I mean, look at the way he's dressing.

831
01:04:15,751 --> 01:04:17,776
Look, Lieutenant, I vouch for him.

832
01:04:17,887 --> 01:04:21,618
Jesus Himself could vouch for him.
You know what it's gonna be with I. A...

833
01:04:21,724 --> 01:04:25,524
"What are we doing? Hosting this guy's
long booze and broad party?"

834
01:04:25,628 --> 01:04:28,893
It's just a matter of one break.
He's high and tight with Troiano.

835
01:04:28,998 --> 01:04:31,831
Tell your boss that he took him
to a meeting with Allie Boy.

836
01:04:31,934 --> 01:04:34,061
Now, that establishes a connection.

837
01:04:34,170 --> 01:04:35,865
We're getting close.

838
01:04:35,972 --> 01:04:38,702
I understand, Mike,
but you're not getting the message.

839
01:04:39,308 --> 01:04:42,709
You're running out of time.
This thing dries up, it falls on you.

840
01:04:42,812 --> 01:04:43,779
I know that.

841
01:04:43,880 --> 01:04:46,678
Your proposal, your project,
your responsibility.

842
01:04:46,782 --> 01:04:49,012
If your boy ends up
on the wrong side of I.A.,

843
01:04:49,118 --> 01:04:50,585
that's gonna come to you too.

844
01:04:53,256 --> 01:04:56,089
You need to press it
or pull your man out.

845
01:05:03,532 --> 01:05:06,660
<i>Christ, Andy, you are not
helping the Miami P.D.</i>

846
01:05:06,769 --> 01:05:09,829
Or the Feds dressing like
Calvin Klein here.

847
01:05:09,939 --> 01:05:11,031
Not to mention I.A.

848
01:05:11,140 --> 01:05:14,632
Come on, Mike, Chris wants me
to fit in with the people we deal with.

849
01:05:14,744 --> 01:05:18,612
Like the dead Russians in the BMw...
is that what you call fitting in?

850
01:05:18,714 --> 01:05:20,238
What's that supposed to mean?

851
01:05:20,349 --> 01:05:23,182
It means this: I put a guy's picture
on a bulletin board,

852
01:05:23,286 --> 01:05:26,278
he's nobody to me...
he's a bad guy, fine, I nail him.

853
01:05:26,389 --> 01:05:30,223
I gotta spend some time with him...
interrogation, courthouse, this, that...

854
01:05:30,326 --> 01:05:33,591
I wind up saying, "It's a shame
the guy's a hood. He's good company. "

855
01:05:33,696 --> 01:05:35,755
I'm not spending every day
with him like you.

856
01:05:35,865 --> 01:05:39,392
- You know what I'm sayin'?
- No. I don't have a clue.

857
01:05:39,502 --> 01:05:42,266
I mean, he's no picture
on a bulletin board to you, Andy.

858
01:05:42,371 --> 01:05:46,000
He's a real flesh-and-blood guy,
and that can be dangerous.

859
01:05:46,108 --> 01:05:49,475
- Are they asking questions about me?
- The question has come up.

860
01:05:49,578 --> 01:05:51,739
They wonder if you're
getting too involved.

861
01:05:51,847 --> 01:05:53,144
Once the case is made,

862
01:05:53,249 --> 01:05:56,980
it's good night to the amazing girls
every night at the club, the nice clothes...

863
01:05:57,086 --> 01:05:58,917
once the bust comes, the party's over.

864
01:05:59,021 --> 01:06:02,422
The party's my job!
I can handle this thing.

865
01:06:02,525 --> 01:06:05,289
I believe you.
But we're out of time, Andy.

866
01:06:07,096 --> 01:06:10,361
Your boy Troiano, he's about
to have a meltdown any minute.

867
01:06:10,933 --> 01:06:11,900
Why?

868
01:06:12,001 --> 01:06:14,595
Well, you remember Davey Harris?

869
01:06:15,638 --> 01:06:19,233
- Yeah, the Russians mentioned him.
- He's an old friend of Chris.

870
01:06:19,342 --> 01:06:21,867
He just got pinched for
drug conspiracy and murder.

871
01:06:21,978 --> 01:06:23,343
He's facing a long time.

872
01:06:23,446 --> 01:06:26,006
And Chris used to run with
the Bath Avenue crew.

873
01:06:26,115 --> 01:06:27,742
"The Binger," they used to call him,

874
01:06:27,850 --> 01:06:31,684
because he did so many crimes...
bank stick-ups, drugs, hot cars...

875
01:06:31,787 --> 01:06:34,187
and maybe even a few murders
for the Allie Boy crew.

876
01:06:34,290 --> 01:06:36,224
According to some new information,

877
01:06:36,325 --> 01:06:40,762
Harris was involved in a homicide
of a Russian housewife a few years ago.

878
01:06:40,863 --> 01:06:43,354
Marina Petrov. Late wife...

879
01:06:43,466 --> 01:06:45,798
- Slava Petrov, yeah.
- Right.

880
01:06:45,901 --> 01:06:47,368
Jesus.

881
01:06:47,470 --> 01:06:50,598
That's why Allie Boy whacked out
the two Russians, then.

882
01:06:50,706 --> 01:06:53,004
The Russians were getting close
to their golden goose,

883
01:06:53,109 --> 01:06:54,440
so Allie Boy had 'em whacked

884
01:06:54,543 --> 01:06:57,137
to protect the money laundering
going through the club.

885
01:06:58,314 --> 01:07:00,612
Look, Andy,
I want you to take this.

886
01:07:02,618 --> 01:07:03,607
Take it.

887
01:07:04,653 --> 01:07:06,450
What, do they want me
to wear a wire?

888
01:07:06,555 --> 01:07:09,888
- They're ready to pull the plug.
- Oh, Mike. Jesus.

889
01:07:09,992 --> 01:07:12,119
The Feds are asking
what we're waiting for,

890
01:07:12,228 --> 01:07:14,389
I.A.'s circling like vultures.

891
01:07:14,497 --> 01:07:16,328
They're all wondering
what we're doing here.

892
01:07:17,566 --> 01:07:19,500
They think I'm holding out?

893
01:07:19,602 --> 01:07:21,661
If Davey Harris rolled
and that's enough...

894
01:07:21,771 --> 01:07:25,730
It's not enough, not with Davey's record.
Nobody's corroborating his story.

895
01:07:27,476 --> 01:07:31,378
Look, whatever Troiano does,
I need it on tape, now.

896
01:07:31,480 --> 01:07:32,947
And I'm not asking.

897
01:07:45,961 --> 01:07:48,429
They picked up your friend
Davey Harris in a sweep.

898
01:07:48,531 --> 01:07:50,089
That's tough luck for Davey.

899
01:07:54,470 --> 01:07:56,529
<i>It doesn't look good
for you, either.</i>

900
01:07:56,639 --> 01:07:58,470
What do you mean by that?

901
01:07:58,574 --> 01:07:59,700
You knew him a long time.

902
01:07:59,809 --> 01:08:02,141
You did things
with this Davey, am I right?

903
01:08:02,244 --> 01:08:04,371
- A long time ago.
- It doesn't matter.

904
01:08:04,480 --> 01:08:05,970
They have him on a conspiracy case

905
01:08:06,082 --> 01:08:08,107
and that shooting
from a long time ago.

906
01:08:08,217 --> 01:08:10,549
He's looking at 25 years to life.

907
01:08:12,354 --> 01:08:14,686
<i>So you figure at some point
he's going to talk,</i>

908
01:08:14,790 --> 01:08:16,883
<i>and then they come looking for you.</i>

909
01:08:16,992 --> 01:08:18,926
You think Davey's gonna roll?

910
01:08:19,962 --> 01:08:21,020
He's 35 years old.

911
01:08:21,130 --> 01:08:24,361
He's facing the rest of his life in prison
with no possibility of parole.

912
01:08:24,467 --> 01:08:25,434
You tell me.

913
01:08:25,534 --> 01:08:30,471
Look, what if I get word to him...
I pay him to keep his mouth shut.

914
01:08:30,573 --> 01:08:32,939
The minute he says a word,
no more paychecks.

915
01:08:33,042 --> 01:08:35,670
The guy's got a family,
and it's worked in the past.

916
01:08:35,778 --> 01:08:38,440
Sure, for 18 months,
even five years,

917
01:08:38,547 --> 01:08:40,538
but not life with no parole.

918
01:08:40,649 --> 01:08:43,777
Maybe he doesn't like
all the success you have in Miami.

919
01:08:43,886 --> 01:08:45,911
- So what? That's my problem.
- Yes, it is.

920
01:08:46,021 --> 01:08:49,013
But your problem could become
our friend's problem very quickly.

921
01:08:49,959 --> 01:08:53,019
You know what?
You don't need to lay this out for me.

922
01:08:53,129 --> 01:08:54,596
It ain't gonna happen.

923
01:08:54,697 --> 01:08:56,187
I hope not.

924
01:08:57,266 --> 01:08:59,393
You have a lot of friends, Chris.

925
01:08:59,502 --> 01:09:01,129
I'd hate to see you closed down.

926
01:09:02,338 --> 01:09:05,899
Yeah? You'd hate to see
the suitcases stop?

927
01:09:06,008 --> 01:09:07,669
No one can deny that.

928
01:09:08,677 --> 01:09:10,975
But whether the suitcases
are there or not...

929
01:09:13,916 --> 01:09:16,817
We will take care of you,
Christopher.

930
01:09:25,427 --> 01:09:26,587
Go, go, go!

931
01:10:28,791 --> 01:10:30,258
- what?
- Come on!

932
01:10:40,169 --> 01:10:42,603
Hey. I'm glad you're still here.
Let's go for a ride.

933
01:10:42,705 --> 01:10:45,003
- Where we goin'?
- I'll tell you in the car.

934
01:10:45,107 --> 01:10:46,074
Come on.

935
01:10:53,649 --> 01:10:56,049
That little blood-sucking scumbag.

936
01:10:56,151 --> 01:10:57,618
After everything I did for him?

937
01:10:57,720 --> 01:11:01,451
I brought him down here.
I gave him a life, some dignity.

938
01:11:01,557 --> 01:11:05,425
He was making money hand over fist,
and he does this to me?

939
01:11:05,527 --> 01:11:08,052
- What did he do?
- Danny Hayes never went back home.

940
01:11:08,163 --> 01:11:10,893
He got a backer, and he's gonna
open up some new megaclub

941
01:11:11,000 --> 01:11:12,365
right down the block from us.

942
01:11:12,468 --> 01:11:13,696
So what?

943
01:11:13,802 --> 01:11:15,667
I want to tear
his tongue out, so what!

944
01:11:15,771 --> 01:11:17,966
I want to whack him so bad
my teeth hurt.

945
01:11:19,575 --> 01:11:22,305
Chris, you gotta use your head
right now, okay?

946
01:11:22,411 --> 01:11:24,879
You got a good thing
going down here.

947
01:11:24,980 --> 01:11:27,813
You go doing something crazy,
you're gonna mess everything up.

948
01:11:28,617 --> 01:11:30,244
I got a job to do.

949
01:11:30,352 --> 01:11:32,820
You with me or not?

950
01:11:36,492 --> 01:11:37,459
You in or out?

951
01:11:38,861 --> 01:11:40,556
I'm here, ain't I?

952
01:11:44,066 --> 01:11:47,058
- Have you got a plan?
- Yeah. I'm gonna go to the front door.

953
01:11:47,169 --> 01:11:50,138
I'm gonna pound on it, and I'm gonna
put the fear of God into him.

954
01:11:50,239 --> 01:11:53,003
He's gonna run out the back,
where you grab him.

955
01:11:53,108 --> 01:11:53,972
I grab him.

956
01:11:54,076 --> 01:11:56,306
What do you want me to do
when I grab him?

957
01:11:56,412 --> 01:11:58,607
You grab him,
I bop him on the head,

958
01:11:58,714 --> 01:12:01,410
We roll him up in a rug,
go feed him to the gators.

959
01:12:06,322 --> 01:12:10,053
Chris, you're talking about risking
spending the rest of your life

960
01:12:10,159 --> 01:12:12,286
in a Florida prison
over this piece of crap?

961
01:12:12,394 --> 01:12:15,761
- That's what you want to do?
- There ain't gonna be any body.

962
01:12:15,864 --> 01:12:16,956
Okay?

963
01:12:19,601 --> 01:12:22,331
- You goin' soft on me?
- I'm not going soft on you.

964
01:12:22,438 --> 01:12:25,236
Just don't go shooting up
the neighborhood like wyatt Earp.

965
01:12:25,341 --> 01:12:26,933
Nobody's shooting anybody.

966
01:12:27,042 --> 01:12:30,034
We hit him over the head,
we dump him, we're done with it.

967
01:12:32,281 --> 01:12:33,441
All right.

968
01:12:35,017 --> 01:12:36,507
This is the street right up here.

969
01:12:52,534 --> 01:12:53,501
Hey.

970
01:12:54,536 --> 01:12:56,436
What are you waiting for?

971
01:12:56,538 --> 01:12:58,165
Let's go, let's do this.

972
01:13:04,580 --> 01:13:05,945
Go around back.

973
01:13:08,484 --> 01:13:09,678
Hurry up.

974
01:13:13,555 --> 01:13:14,817
Hey, Danny!

975
01:13:14,923 --> 01:13:17,551
Danny, come on out!
we need to talk!

976
01:13:20,462 --> 01:13:23,124
Come on! Danny!

977
01:13:23,232 --> 01:13:24,824
Open up!

978
01:13:27,936 --> 01:13:29,927
Danny, come on, open up!
It's me!

979
01:13:31,473 --> 01:13:33,270
Come on! Come on!

